			<div class="content" id="post-content-4819456">
									

<div style="text-align: justify;">
<p>It's November 15th. The world is getting colder. Snow is beginning to grace the ground. Thanksgiving is soon. Christmas, Hanukkah, Kwanzaa, Yule, and a whole assortment of other holidays are soon to follow. But first, we have our own, special, SCP only holiday to celebrate. It's actually a whole festival, that starts today, and ends on Dec. 29th. It's called&#8230;</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1><span><span style="font-size:140%;"><strong>The SCP Holiday Art Exchange~!</strong></span></span></h1>
<p>(hosted by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;">DarkStuff</a></span> with his lovely assistant, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span>)</p>
</div>
<hr />
<p><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1><span>The Overview</span></h1>
</div>
<p><strong>Hold up, what is this?</strong></p>
<p>Glad you asked! This is an annual event on the SCP wiki in which people exchange gifts, Secret Santa style! The giftee doesn't know who their gifter is until several days after receiving the gift itself, and everyone gets to have a ton of fun making other people happy and being made happy.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Hmm, what kind of gifts can be exchanged?</strong></p>
<p>Gifts can be anything that can be given over the internet, but, due to the community, are most often writing, visual art, or some other kind of media that can be given with a link! Though optional, plenty of the gifts exchanged during the art exchange are later posted as tales or SCPs on the site, or posted onto the respective art pages of the gifting artists.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Y'know, that's pretty neat, I'm in! How do I join?</strong></p>
<p>Glad to have you on board! You can participate by responding to this thread with this format:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>What I Can Give:</strong></p>
<p><strong>What I Am Looking For:</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>And of course fill in after the colons with the respective information. Before you do, however, let me impart onto you some wisdom that has been learned from previous years&#8230; <em>don't</em>, I repeat, <em>don't</em> put that you'd be &quot;alright with anything&quot; in the <em>What I Am Looking For</em> section! You may think that you are being considerate and making the process easier, but this, in fact, is one of the hardest wishes to fulfill, because your giftee will be directionless! Please make it something more specific than that. And speaking of rules&#8230;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Don't sign up if you are iffy on being able to make the deadlines, laid out below!</em></p>
<p>This art exchange runs on a schedule. You will be expected to have a gift ready to turn in by the deadline. If you're unsure you can make that, it'd be best to abstain for this year. That said, if something unexpected comes up in the over-a-month between now and then, we get it and will not blame you. If such a thing were to occur, you have two options:</p>
<ol>
<li>Send in an unfinished gift at the deadline with the promise of finishing it later, or&#8230;</li>
<li>Contact us! Send either me or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span> a PM as soon as possible, and we'll get a pinch-hitter on it right away, no harm no foul. More on that later!</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<p><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1><span>The Schedule</span></h1>
</div>
<p>First, a brief overview.</p>
<p><strong>Nov. 15th - Nov. 28th</strong> &#8212; Gathering participants.<br />
<strong>Nov. 30th - Dec. 22nd</strong> &#8212; Making the gifts.<br />
<strong>Dec. 23rd - Dec. 24th</strong> &#8212; Pinch-hitting.<br />
<strong>Dec. 25th - Dec. 28th</strong> &#8212; Receive gifts, guess at giftees.<br />
<strong>Dec. 29th</strong> &#8212; Revealing the Secret Santas.<br />
<strong>Anytime after Dec. 29th</strong> &#8212; Optional posting of gifts to the wiki.</p>
<p>Now, something more in-depth:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">How&nbsp;It's&nbsp;All&nbsp;Gonna&nbsp;Go</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&amp;&nbsp;When</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Nov. 15th - Nov. 28th</strong> &#8212; <em>Gathering Participants</em></p>
<p>This is the period during which you can reply to this very thread with the &quot;what I can give, what I would like&quot; format. After this period is over, no one more can join, so you're going to have to profess your participation before Nov. 28th, at 21:00 PST!</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Nov. 30th - Dec. 22nd</strong> &#8212; <em>Making the Gifts</em></p>
<p>Between Nov. 28th and Nov. 30th, I (and perhaps <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span>) will be using black magic to determine who will be Secret Santa for who, and on Nov. 30th, we will release a barrage of Wikidot PMs which will secretly enlighten you as to who are making gifts for! When these get sent out will be variable, but look for them on the 30th. As soon as you have your PM, and have been enlightened as to what your giftee wants, it is up to you to create your gift for them!</p>
<p>You may turn in your gift <em>any time</em> between Nov. 30th and Dec. 22nd, but the hard deadline is Dec. 22nd at 21:00 PST. By the way, you may be wondering. How can you keep your writing gift anonymous? Well, you can use <a href="https://pastebin.com/" target="_blank">Pastebin</a> as a text dump just like people can use <a href="https://imgur.com/" target="_blank">Imgur</a> as an image dump. But, if you'd like it to visibly show Wikidot formatting, you can copy the following CSS into a sandbox page:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>[[module css]]<br />
a#history-button, a#files-button {<br />
display: none;<br />
}<br />
[[/module]]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This will make it so that the <em>History</em> button at the bottom of the page doesn't show up, keeping your writing completely anonymous~!</p>
<p><em>How</em> do you turn your gift in? You can turn in your gift by Wikidot PMing either myself or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span> with the gift in question. Please, make it easy on us by saying &quot;my gift for [person]&quot;, so we don't have to search through our own spreadsheet to find out who you made a gift for. And as a reminder, <em>do not ghost the Art Exchange!</em> If you suddenly realize you can't make the deadline, <em>tell us</em>. There is no shame in realizing it isn't going to work out. There <em>is</em> a little bit in dropping off the face of the earth with no warning. So please just say!</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Dec. 23rd - Dec. 24th</strong> &#8212; <em>Pinch-Hitting</em></p>
<p>During this time, I and others (the pinch-hitters) will work to fill in for any gifters that didn't make the deadline. It's hectic, we may end up with works in progress instead of finished products, but it will happen, and we will work together to ensure the most holiday joy possible.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Dec. 25th - Dec. 28th</strong> &#8212; <em>Receive Gifts, Guess at Giftees</em></p>
<p>At some time during Christmas day, Dec. 25th, every lovely participant will receive their gift anonymously via a PM from myself or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605590655" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span>. We encourage you to post <em>here</em>, on this thread, with a link to your gift, and your own thoughts on it! Then, people can experience everyone's gifts together, and we can revel in guessing at who made what!</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Dec. 29th</strong> &#8212; <em>Revealing Secret Santas</em></p>
<p>On Dec. 29th, at 10:00 PST, I will reveal who made what gifts with a post here on this thread. Then everyone can talk to their giftees, discuss the aftermath, celebrate, what have you, et cetera and onward! It's a great big occasion and it's tons of fun to see if your guess was correct, or if you were completely off the mark. Plus, you can then talk to your giftees about perhaps some revisions before it goes up on the site, if going up on the site is a plan. Speaking of&#8230;</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Anytime after Dec. 29th</strong> &#8212; <em>Optional Posting of Gifts to the Wiki</em></p>
<p>If your gift that you gave fits on the wiki, as a tale or SCP or GoI format, then I encourage you to post when you are ready! Remember to add the tag &quot;<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/system:page-tags/tag/art-exchange#pages" target="_blank">art-exchange</a>&quot;, and then link to your piece in the <a href="/art-exchange-hub">Art Exchange Hub</a>, under the 2020 section! Oh, and we'll be doing something new this year&#8230;</p>
<p>The second most common type of gift to give and receive in this art exchange is visual art, so we're going to add a section to the hub for all the visual art that gets shared here! We're not exactly sure of the format yet, but be on the lookout for that, because we will know what we're doing and how <em>you</em> can add your art to it by Dec. 29th, and will edit those instructions into this here post. Wowza!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1><span>Pinch-Hitting &amp; Friendly Reminders</span></h1>
</div>
<p><strong>About being a pinch-hitter.</strong></p>
<p>Pinch-hitters are the people who have from Dec. 23rd to Dec. 24th to create a gift for giftees who have absentee gifters. You may have more than this amount of time if a gifter reveals they won't be able to make it some time <em>before</em> the deadline, but worst case (and most likely) scenario, you will have 48 hours to create (or make headway into) a gift, which means&#8230;</p>
<p><em>Don't</em> become a pinch-hitter unless you are <em>very</em> confident in your ability! On top of that, I may refuse you as a pinch-hitter if I don't think you can do it. Harsh, I know, but the only way <em>I</em> can be confident in you is if you're known and I know you (or you can be vouched for). It's all in the aid of getting everyone gifts they can be happy with, on-time. If you would like to be a pinch-hitter, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">simply say so at the bottom of your post you make on this thread.</span></p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Final, friendly reminders!</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><em>Don't ghost the exchange.</em> Please, if you can't make it, send a PM <em>beforehand.</em></li>
<li>It's called <em>Secret</em> Santa! Don't reveal yourself to your giftee, and if you know something, don't let anyone in on it! Secrecy is part of the fun!</li>
<li>Keep it jolly and festive! Don't intentionally make a gift that goes against the giftee's wishes, or otherwise knowingly make something bad.</li>
<li>Oh, and no smut please. The content on this site can definitely end up in the NSFW <em>zone</em>, but very few people are here for erotica, and last year there was an issue with that, so we're making it a rule!</li>
</ul>
<p>Alright, with all of that out of the way&#8230;</p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1><span><span style="font-size:140%;"><strong>Let the Merriment Begin~!</strong></span></span></h1>
</div>
</div>

